videos.description: Baylor's Jo Lual-Acuil Jr. knocks West Virginia's Jevon Carter to the ground with a strong screen to give Manu Lecomte enough space for an easy lay-in.
videos.headline: Baylor uses punishing screen to set up score

videos.description: With the shot clock winding down, West Virginia's Jevon Carter hits a pull-up 3 from well beyond the arc as the buzzer sounds.
videos.headline: Carter connects from way downtown to beat shot clock

videos.description: Baylor's Jo Lual-Acuil Jr. goes up for a lay-in, but West Virginia's Sagaba Konate rises up to swat the shot away with authority.
videos.headline: WVU's Konate rejects shot at the rim

videos.description: West Virginia's Esa Ahmad pokes the ball loose on defense and finishes in transition with a thunderous one-handed dunk.
videos.headline: Mountaineers steal and slam

videos.description: In the final seconds of the half, WVU's Jevon Carter shoots from beyond half court and connects, giving the Mountaineers a 29-23 lead at the half.
videos.headline: Carter swishes three-quarter court heave to close 1st half

videos.description: West Virginia head coach Bob Huggins says his team was able to overcome a slow start by focusing on better ball movement and off-ball cuts.
videos.headline: Huggins credits fundamentals for first-half run

videos.description: Mountaineers guard Daxter Miles Jr. goes on a personal 9-0 run, hitting three consecutive shots from beyond the arc to give WVU a double-digit lead.
videos.headline: WVU's Miles drains 3 straight triples

videos.description: Bears forward Mark Vital comes up with a monster block on West Virginia's Jevon Carter, sending his shot off the backboard and out of bounds.
videos.headline: Baylor's Vital swats shot off glass

videos.description: After a whistle, Mountaineers guard Jevon Carter wanders over to Baylor's huddle and tries to blend in before Bears forward Jo Lual-Acuil Jr. pushes him away.
videos.headline: West Virginia's Carter sneaks into Baylor's huddle

videos.description: Mountaineers forward Esa Ahmad drives baseline and elevates for a huge one-handed jam over Baylor's Jo Lual-Acuil Jr. for the hoop and the harm.
videos.headline: WVU's Ahmad throws down vicious and-1 dunk

videos.description: With the shot clock winding down, Manu Lecomte's shot gets stuck on the rim for several seconds before the ball drops in for a Baylor score.
videos.headline: Lecomte's shot stalls on the rim then falls in

videos.description: Mountaineer forward Esa Ahmad picks off a pass and finishes with a one-handed dunk to put an exclamation mark on West Virginia's 78-65 win over Baylor.
videos.headline: Ahmad's slam caps West Virginia win

videos.description: Esa Ahmad leads the Mountaineers with 21 points while Jevon Carter adds 18 points and 11 assists in a 78-65 win against the Bears.
videos.headline: West Virginia beats Baylor, onto Big 12 semis
